---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout title="TestGenerator">
  <h1>TestGenerator</h1>

  <p>Auto-generates diverse test cases from an agent spec, with intent tracing and diversity enforcement.</p>

  <h2>Interface</h2>
  <pre><code>import &lcub; TestGenerator &rcub; from "agent-forge/test_generator";
import &lcub; createOllamaBackend &rcub; from "agent-forge/llm_backend/ollama";

const llm = createOllamaBackend();
const tg = new TestGenerator(llm);

const testCases = await tg.generate(&lcub;
  description: "review PRs for logic errors and style violations",
  inputSchema: &lcub; pr_url: "string", repo: "string" &rcub;,
  outputSchema: &lcub; issues: "array", score: "number", summary: "string" &rcub;,
  tools: ["gh_api", "read_file"],
  k: 5,
&rcub;);

const coverage = tg.checkCoverage(testCases, description);
// coverage.gaps = ["style violations"] if not covered</code></pre>

  <h2>TestCase Structure</h2>
  <pre><code>interface TestCase &lcub;
  id: string;
  input: unknown;
  expectedSchema: &lcub; keys: string[] &rcub;;
  tracedTo: string[];       // description clauses this test covers
  diversityScore: number;   // 0.0-1.0, how unique this test is
&rcub;</code></pre>

  <h2>Diversity Enforcement</h2>
  <p>After parsing the LLM-generated test cases, pairwise Jaccard similarity is computed:</p>
  <pre><code>function jaccardSimilarity(a: unknown, b: unknown): number &lcub;
  const aStr = JSON.stringify(a);
  const bStr = JSON.stringify(b);
  if (aStr equals bStr) return 1;
  const aSet = new Set(aStr.split(""));
  const bSet = new Set(bStr.split(""));
  const intersection = [...aSet].filter(c equals bSet.has(c)).length;
  const union = new Set([...aSet, ...bSet]).size;
  return intersection / union;  // greater than 0.7 = too similar, rejected
&rcub;</code></pre>
  <p>If fewer than <code>k</code> diverse tests are generated, fallback synthetic tests are appended.</p>

  <h2>Intent Tracing</h2>
  <p>The NL description is parsed for key aspects using regex patterns:</p>
  <pre><code>const aspectPatterns = [
  &lcub; pattern: /logic\s*errors?/gi, aspect: "logic errors" &rcub;,
  &lcub; pattern: /style\s*violations?/gi, aspect: "style violations" &rcub;,
  &lcub; pattern: /test\s*coverage/gi, aspect: "test coverage" &rcub;,
  &lcub; pattern: /security/gi, aspect: "security" &rcub;,
  &lcub; pattern: /performance/gi, aspect: "performance" &rcub;,
];</code></pre>
  <p>Each test's <code>tracedTo</code> field maps it to the aspects it exercises. <code>checkCoverage()</code> then identifies any aspect with zero test coverage.</p>

  <h2>CoverageReport</h2>
  <pre><code>interface CoverageReport &lcub;
  aspects: string[];         // all aspects found in description
  coveredAspects: string[];  // aspects with tests
  gaps: string[];             // aspects with 0 tests - BLOCKS export
&rcub;</code></pre>

  <h2>JSON Parsing Robustness</h2>
  <p>If the LLM output fails to parse as JSON, fallback test cases are generated:</p>
  <pre><code>// Fallback generates k placeholder tests
// with structurally valid but generic inputs
// matching the inputSchema keys</code></pre>
</Layout>
